# Analysis of Main Target Image

## Block Count & Layers
The structure uses 12 building blocks arranged in approximately 3-4 layers.

## Spatial Relationships
The structure consists of:
- Bottom layer: A green rectangular block (#8) with a blue cube (#5) and yellow cube (#7) beside it, and an orange triangular block (#15) on the far left
- Middle layer: A vertical orange cylinder (#9) in the center, with a red curved piece (#2) extending to the right with two more curved sections (#3, #1)
- Top layer: A red arch structure (#4) with a circular opening on top of the cylinder, topped with two yellow dome pieces (#12)
- A blue cube (#5) sits on top of the right red curved section

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on the main image, I need the following blocks:
- Block #1: Red arch piece (right end of curved track)
- Block #2: Red curved piece (middle part of track)
- Block #3: Red curved piece (left part of track)
- Block #4: Red arch with circular opening (top structure)
- Block #5: Blue cube (two of these - one next to yellow cube, one on curved track)
- Block #6: Green cube (not visible in final structure)
- Block #7: Yellow cube (part of bottom layer)
- Block #8: Green rectangular block (bottom layer)
- Block #9: Vertical orange cylinder (center support)
- Block #12: Yellow dome piece (two of these on top of red arch)
- Block #15: Orange triangular block (left side)

# Assembly Order

```

}
```
